Israeli Stocks: Enlight Renewable Energy, Medigus and Teva

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-05-02T14:26:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/israeli-stocks-enlight-renewable-energy-medigus-and-teva.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index declined for a
fifth day, losing 0.3 percent to 1,291.89 at the 4:30 p.m. close
in Tel Aviv. Investors traded about 1.57 billion shekels ($466
million) in shares and convertible securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Enlight Renewable Energy Ltd. (ENLT)   advanced the most
since April 21, gaining 1.9 percent to 0.428 shekel. The board
of the developer of photovoltaic systems approved a bond
offering of as much as 50 million shekels.  Medigus Ltd. (MDGS)   rose the most since January 16,
climbing 4.7 percent to 1.036 shekels. The maker of medical
devices to treat gastroesophageal reflux disease completed
development of a second-generation video camera.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)   jumped 3.5
percent, the most since December 2010, to 161.2 shekels. The
world’s biggest maker of generic drugs agreed to buy Cephalon
Inc. for $6.8 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  